  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Merchandiser",
  "description": "<p>Sales Merchandiser</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Conduct regular store visits to ensure merchandising guidelines are followed and products are presented with high quality. Manage orders and stock levels to reduce out-of-stock situations. Build strong relationships and negotiate for optimal product display in retail stores.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct regular store visits to verify compliance with merchandising guidelines and maintain product presentation standards</li><li>Take customer orders and track stock movement to minimize out-of-stock situations</li><li>Build and maintain positive working relationships with store personnel to support sales objectives</li><li>Negotiate with store personnel to secure better display positions and additional shelf space for products</li><li>Visit retail stores across Singapore as assigned to perform merchandising and sales activities</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in the FMCG industry is an advantage</li><li>Demonstrate self-motivation and initiative to work independently</li><li>Exhibit strong interpersonal and communication skills to engage effectively with store personnel</li><li>Apply organizational and time management skills to manage multiple store visits and tasks efficiently</li><li>Use negotiation skills to improve product placement and visibility</li><li>Maintain a positive attitude and work collaboratively as a team player</li></ul><p>Benefits:</p><ul><li>5-day work week</li><li>Commission</li><li>Transport allowance (reimbursement)</li><li>Annual leave</li><li>Medical benefits</li><li>Annual Wage Supplement (A.W.S.)</li></ul>",
